📅 6+ Month Full-Feature Development Timeline
Broken into monthly phases, weekly tasks, mapped to all 17 modules + SaaS features

🗓️ Month 1: Foundation & Multi-Tenancy Setup (Weeks 1-4)
Goal: Working multi-tenant Laravel 11 app with base auth

Week 1: Project Initialization
Init Git repo, configure .env (MySQL, mail, queue)
Install Laravel 11.x: composer create-project laravel/laravel .
Install + configure stancl/tenancy v3: central DB (super admin) + per-tenant DB strategy, domain resolution, tenant middleware
Week 2: Auth & RBAC Setup
Install Laravel Breeze (Blade + Livewire stack)
Configure multi-auth guards: super_admin, school_admin, teacher, student, parent
Install spatie/laravel-permission, set up base roles/permissions
Week 3: Base Middleware & Tenant Scoping
Build tenant subscription check middleware
Configure tenant-aware migrations (central vs tenant DBs)
Set up base Blade layouts for super admin and tenant panels
Week 4: Testing & Validation
Write feature tests for tenant creation, auth flows
Verify tenant data isolation
Run php artisan pint (linting) and php artisan test (Pest)
🗓️ Month 2: SaaS Super Admin Panel (Weeks 5-8)
Goal: Functional super admin panel to manage schools/tenants

Week 5: Central DB Migrations & Models
Create central tables: tenants, domains, subscription_packages, subscriptions, payments
Build Tenant, SubscriptionPackage, Domain models (central)
Week 6: Tenant & Subscription Management
Super admin CRUD for tenants (schools): activate/deactivate, trial periods
Subscription package management: Free/Basic/Premium, feature limits
Domain mapping: Subdomains (e.g., school1.sms-erp.com) or custom domains
Week 7: Payment Gateway Evaluation & Integration
Evaluate Stripe/Razorpay/PayPal (align with target market)
Integrate selected gateway for subscription billing
Build payment webhooks, invoice generation
Week 8: Super Admin Dashboard & Testing
Global analytics: Active schools, revenue, user counts
Global settings panel
Feature tests for super admin flows
🗓️ Month 3: School Core Modules (Tenant Side) (Weeks 9-12)
Goal: Core school setup and Student Information System (Module 2, 3)

Week 9: Tenant School Setup
Tenant-scoped migrations for school profile, branding, academic years
School branding: Logo, colors, custom domain configuration
Academic year setup, class/section management
Week 10: Student Information System (SIS)
Student admission flow, profile management, document upload
ID card generation (PDF via dompdf)
Class allocation, promotion/transfer, alumni management
Week 11: Academic & Attendance Basics (Modules 5, 6)
Subject, curriculum, timetable management (conflict-free scheduling)
Student/staff attendance (manual + biometric/RFID integration prep)
Attendance reports
Week 12: Tenant RBAC & Testing
Per-school role assignment (school admin, teacher, student, parent)
Feature tests for tenant SIS and academic flows
🗓️ Month 4: Academic & Examination Modules (Weeks 13-16)
Goal: Admission, lesson planning, exam system (Modules 4, 5, 7)

Week 13: Admission Management
Online admission inquiry, lead management
Entrance test scheduling, document verification, approval workflow
Week 14: Lesson Planning & Assignments
Lesson plan creation, homework/assignment management
Online classes/LMS integration prep (optional)
Week 15: Examination & Results
Exam setup, marks entry, grade system configuration
PDF report card generation, result analytics
Week 16: Testing & Validation
Feature tests for admission, exam, and academic modules
Verify tenant data isolation for all new modules
🗓️ Month 5: Finance, HR & Payroll (Weeks 17-20)
Goal: Fee, accounting, HR/payroll (Modules 8, 9, 10)

Week 17: Fee Management
Fee structure setup, online/offline fee collection
Discounts, scholarships, late fees, receipt generation
Week 18: Accounting & Finance
Income/expense tracking, ledger/journal entries
Vendor management, balance sheet, audit reports
Week 19: HR & Payroll
Staff management, attendance/leave tracking
Salary structure, payroll processing, PF/ESI integration
Week 20: Testing
Feature tests for finance and HR modules
Verify payment gateway integration for fee collection
🗓️ Month 6: Additional Modules (Weeks 21-24)
Goal: Transport, Library, Hostel, Inventory (Modules 12, 13, 14, 15)

Week 21: Transport Management
Route/stop management, vehicle tracking, transport fees
Driver details, vehicle maintenance logs
Week 22: Library Management
Book inventory, issue/return, barcode system, fine calculation
Week 23: Hostel & Inventory
Hostel room allocation, mess management, complaints
Inventory/asset management, stock tracking, purchase orders
Week 24: Testing
Feature tests for all additional modules
🗓️ Month 7+: Advanced Features & Launch (Weeks 25+)
Goal: Reports, mobile API, white label, optimization (Modules 11, 16, 17 + SaaS features)

Weeks 25-26: Reports & Analytics
Custom dashboards for all roles (super admin, school admin, teacher, student, parent)
Student, fee, attendance, financial reports (PDF export)
Weeks 27-28: Mobile App API
RESTful API via Laravel Sanctum for multi-role mobile apps
API documentation (Swagger/OpenAPI)
Weeks 29-30: White Label & Scalability
Per-school custom branding, custom domains
Scalability testing: Add unlimited schools, centralized updates
Weeks 31-32: Optimization & Deployment
Performance tuning, queue setup for notifications/emails
Linting (pint), static analysis (phpstan), full test suite
Deploy to production
